bug.short_desc: [regression] review editor shows SUBM category that is not displayed in web UI

long_desc.thetext: When a review is submitted a "SUBM" category is displayed in the Reviewers section. This category is redundant with the status and confusing because doesn't have a proper label. The web UI does not show the category hence it should be hidden from the review editor.
Yep, I noticed that one as well. Seems that it is suppressed by the Web UI some how. Should be easy enough to get rid of it -- unless it provides some information that isn't surfaced elsewhere?

(In reply to comment #2) > Yep, I noticed that one as well. Seems that it is suppressed by the Web UI some > how. Should be easy enough to get rid of it -- unless it provides some > information that isn't surfaced elsewhere?
I don't think so. I would hide all categories that don't have a proper label or something along those lines.
